{"title_page": "Greene-Rose Heritage Park", "text_new": "{{Infobox park\n| name           = Greene-Rose Heritage Park\n| image          = Green Rose Heritage Park (Cambridge, MA) - DSC00140.JPG\n| image_size     = \n| image_alt      = \n| image_caption  = The park in 2011\n| map            = <!-- or | map_image = --> \n| map_width      = \n| type           = [[Heritage centre|Heritage Park]]\n| location       = \n| nearest_city   = [[Cambridge, Massachusetts]]\n| coordinates    = {{Coord|42.36611|-71.09475|type:landmark_region:US-MA|display=title, inline}}\n| area           = \n| created        = 2008\n| operator       = \n| visitation_num = \n| status         = \n| designation    = \n| open           = \n}}\n\n[[File:Cambridge, MA (2019) - 10.jpg|thumb|Park signage, 2019]]\n'''Greene-Rose Heritage Park''' is a park in [[Cambridge, Massachusetts]], United States. Opened in 2008, the park is located along Harvard Street, near the intersection with Moore Street.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cambridgema.gov/CDD/parks/parksinfo/Parks/greenrosepark|title=Greene-Rose Heritage Park - CDD - City of Cambridge, Massachusetts|website=www.cambridgema.gov}}</ref> It has a playground and tennis courts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bostonmagazine.com/health/2013/06/05/boston-public-tennis-courts/|title=Roundup: Boston Public Tennis Courts|date=June 5, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Commons category-inline|Greene-Rose Heritage Park}}\n\n[[Category:2008 establishments in Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:Cambridge, Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:Parks in Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:Protected areas established in 2008]]\n\n\n{{Massachusetts-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox park\n| name           = Greene-Rose Heritage Park\n| image          = Green Rose Heritage Park (Cambridge, MA) - DSC00140.JPG\n| image_size     = \n| image_alt      = \n| image_caption  = The park in 2011\n| map            = <!-- or | map_image = --> \n| map_width      = \n|