, Lacey Township committeeman<ref name=RichterEndorsementsLacey/>\n* Nick Juliano, Lacey Township committeeman<ref name=RichterEndorsementsLacey/>\n* Tim McDonald, Lacey Township committeeman<ref name=RichterEndorsementsLacey/>\n* John Novak, mayor of Barnegat Township<ref>{{cite web |title=Novak drops from NJ-03 primary, endorses Richter |url=https://savejersey.com/2020/04/novak-drops-from-nj-03-primary-endorses-richter/ |website=Save Jersey |language=en}}</ref>\n;Party Chairs and Leadership\n* Frank B. Holman III, chairman of the [[Ocean County, New Jersey|Ocean County]] Republican Party<ref>{{cite web |last1=Larsen |first1=Erik |title=Ocean County GOP chairman to Republicans: Get behind David Richter for Congress |url=https://www.app.com/story/news/local/ocean-county/2020/03/07/ocean-county-gop-chairman-republicans-get-behind-david-richter-congress/4986980002/ |website=Asbury Park Press |accessdate=10 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n;Organizations\n* Stafford Conservative Republican Club<ref>{{cite web |title=Richter nabs Stafford GOP endorsement |url=https://newjerseyglobe.com/congress/richter-nabs-stafford-gop-endorsement/ |website=New Jersey Globe |accessdate=1 March 2020 |date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n* Berkeley Township Republican Club<ref name=RichterEndorsementsBerkeley/>\n* Berkeley Township Women\u2019s Republican Club<ref name=RichterEndorsementsBerkeley/>\n* Berkeley Township Republican Municipal Committee<ref name=RichterEndorsementsBerkeley/>\n* Brick Township Republican Club<ref name=RichterEndorsementsBrickLacey>{{cite web |title=Brick and Lacey GOP Clubs Issue Unanimous Endorsements of David Richter for Congress |url=https://www.insidernj.com/press-release/brick-lacey-gop-clubs-issue-unanimous-endorsements-david-richter-congress/ |website=Insider NJ |accessdate=2 April 2020 |date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Lacey Township Republican Club<ref name=RichterEndorsementsBrickLacey/>\n}}\n\n===General election===\n====Polling====\n====Endorsements====\n====Results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = New Jersey's 3rd congressional district, 2020\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Andy Kim (politician)|Andy Kim]] (incumbent)\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = TBA\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = \n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==District 4==\n{{see also|New Jersey's 4th congressional district}}\nThe 4th district encompasses the [[Monmouth County, New Jersey|Monmouth County]] area and extends into eastern [[Mercer County, New Jersey|Mercer County]] and northern [[Ocean County, New Jersey|Ocean County]], including [[Lakewood, New Jersey|Lakewood]], [[Tinton Falls, New Jersey|Tinton Falls]], and [[Hamilton Township, Mercer County, New Jersey|Hamilton]]. The incumbent is Republican [[Chris Smith (New Jersey politician)|Chris Smith]], who was re-elected with 55.4% of the vote in 2018.<ref name=\"HPVT\" />\n\n===Republican primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Declared=====\n*Alter Richter \n*[[Chris Smith (New Jersey politician)|Chris Smith]], incumbent U.S. Representative<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wildstein |first1=David |title=Chris Smith will run for re-election in 2020 |url=https://newjerseyglobe.com/congress/chris-smith-will-run-for-re-election-in-2020/ |website=New Jersey Globe |accessdate=August 5, 2019 |date=August 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Primary Results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Republican primary results\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Alter Richter \n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Chris Smith (New Jersey politician)|Chris Smith]] (incumbent)\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n